introduction.p:
          The graph of a function f is given in .  

The graph of f(x).


A piecewise linear graph on an x–y coordinate plane. The graph starts near (–4.5, 4.5) and slopes downward to a low point at about (–1, 1). From there it rises 
sharply to a peak around (1, 5), then slopes downward again to roughly (4, 3). The axes are labeled x and y, with gridlines visible.


\begin{tikzpicture}[thick,scale=0.9] [domain=-5:5]
\draw[step=1cm,color=gray!50] (-5,-2) grid (5,5);
   \draw [black!80,line width=0.3pt,-latex] (0,0) -- (5,0) node [below] at (4.75,0) {$x$};
   \draw [black!80,line width=0.3pt,-latex] (0,0) -- (-5,0);
   \draw [black!80,line width=0.3pt,-latex] (0,0) -- (0,5) node [right] at (0,4.75) {$y$};
   \draw [black!80,line width=0.3pt,-latex] (0,0) -- (0,-2);
\draw[color=blue, line width=2pt,domain=-5:-1]   plot (\x,{-\x});
\draw[color=blue, line width=2pt,domain=-1:1]   plot (\x,{2*\x+3});
\draw[color=blue, line width=2pt,domain=1:5]   plot (\x,{-0.5*\x+5.5});
\foreach \x/\xtext in {-4/-4, -3/-3, -2/-2, -1/-1, 1/1, 2/2, 3/3, 4/4}
    \draw[shift={(\x,0)}] (0pt,3pt) -- (0pt,-3pt) node[below] {$\xtext$};
\foreach \y/\ytext in { -1/-1, 1/1, 2/2, 3/3, 4/4}
    \draw[shift={(0,\y)}] (-2pt,0pt) -- (2pt,0pt) node[left] {$\ytext$};
\end{tikzpicture}

